  levelNumber: 24
  levelName: Calakmul
  location: Campeche, Mexico
  levelDescription: "In the jungle\u2019s heart, Calakmul rose as the Snake Kingdom\u2019s
    mighty capital.\n\nCalakmul, deep in the jungles of Campeche, was one of the
    most powerful Maya capitals during the Classic Period (c. 250\u2013900 AD). Its
    name means \u201CCity of the Two Adjacent Pyramids\u201D, and at its peak it
    controlled a vast kingdom with alliances and rivalries stretching across the
    Maya world.\r\n\r\nThe site contains more than 6,000 structures, making it one
    of the largest Maya cities ever discovered. Its centerpiece is Structure II,
    a massive pyramid rising about 55 meters, one of the tallest in the Maya region.
    Calakmul was the seat of the Kaan (\u201CSnake\u201D) dynasty, fierce rivals
    of Tikal, and its rulers expanded influence through warfare, diplomacy, and trade.\r\n\r\nArchaeologists
    have uncovered richly carved stelae, murals, and tombs that reveal Calakmul\u2019s
    dynastic history and its role as a superpower of the lowlands. Today, hidden
    within the Calakmul Biosphere Reserve, the ruins stand surrounded by tropical
    forest teeming with wildlife, a reminder of the city\u2019s grandeur and its
    enduring connection to nature."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 96fe4944313d18d409facb3e4108211f, type: 3}
